{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"Done. The re-normalization half of the format-drift roadmap item is implemented, tested, and documented. Nothing committed (as instructed).\n\n## What shipped (0.6.0)\n\n**`cledger renormalize`** (+ library `renormalize(repo)`) turns preserved `unrecognized` events this version can now interpret into proper `conversation_turn`s, each with a `supersession` event linking back to the raw placeholder.\n\n**How the id is reconstructed (the crux, constraint 2):** each adapter now exports `renormalizeUnrecognized(event, identity)`, a thin wrapper that re-feeds the stored `raw.data` through the *same* private `convertLine` the live capture loop uses, with the identity-determining inputs recovered from the preserved event:\n- **claude-code**: `conversation.seq`, session id from the line, `occurred_at` from the line's timestamp (timestampless lines can't convert, so they stay preserved).\n- **codex**: `conversation.seq`, session id from `producer.session_id`, and `event.occurred_at` as the `baseTime` fallback — which is exactly the `sessionBaseTime` a live capture of the same rollout file would compute.\n\nSo the turn gets the byte-identical id a live capture would produce, and a later live capture dedups instead of duplicating.\n\n**Design constraints honored:**\n- *Append-only + idempotent* — the `unrecognized` event is never deleted; re-runs skip already-superseded targets, and all produced ids (turn + supersession) are deterministic, so anything that slips through dedups. An `existingIds` guard also blocks the cross-anchor duplicate case (`appendEvents` only dedups within one anchor).\n- *Redaction* — works from the already-redacted stored `raw.data` and rides the normal `appendEvents` redaction path (idempotent on placeholders); nothing re-exposed.\n- *Reasoning policy* — Codex `reasoning` is never preserved and `convertLine` refuses it regardless; no provider-withheld content is ever reconstr